{"title_page": "List of Twenty20 cricket records", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\nThis is a '''list of Twenty20 men's cricket records''', that is a [[world record|record]] team or individual performances in [[Twenty20 cricket]] (T20). The records only include top-level T20 games: those played in officially recognised tournaments in ICC Full-member countries or any [[Twenty20 International]].\n\n==Listing criteria==\nIn general the top five are listed in each category (except when there is a tie for the last place among the five, when all the tied record holders are noted). Currently active players are indicated with a \u2020. Teams playing at home are indicated by (H), where appropriate.\n\n==Team records==\n===Highest innings totals===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank !! Score \n!Team!! Opponent !! Venue !! Date\n|-\n| rowspan=2|1\n| 278/3 (20 overs)\n| {{cr|AFG}}\n| {{cr|IRE}}\n| [[Rajiv Gandhi International Cricket Stadium, Dehradun|Dehradun]]\n| 23 February 2019\n|-\n|278/4 (20 overs)\n|{{cr|CZE}}\n|{{cr|TUR}}\n| Ilfov County\n|30 August 2019\n|-\n| 2\n| 267/2 (20 overs)\n| [[Trinbago Knight Riders]] \n| [[Jamaica Tallawahs]]  (H)\n| [[Sabina Park|Kingston, Jamaica]]\n| 13 September 2019\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 3\n| 263/5 (20 overs)\n| [[Royal Challengers Bangalore]] (H)\n| [[Pune Warriors India]]\n| [[M. Chinnaswamy Stadium|Bangalore]]\n| 23 April 2013\n|-\n| 263/3 (20 overs)\n| {{cr|AUS}}\n| {{cr|SL}} (H)\n| [[Pallekele International Cricket Stadium|Pallekele]]\n| 6 September 2016\n|-\n|colspan=\"6\"| <small>Source: [http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/305298.html ESPNcricinfo] (updated 13 September 2019).</small>\n|}\n\n===Lowest innings totals===\n\nCompleted innings only.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank !! Score !! Team !! Opponent !! Venue !! Date\n|-\n| 1 || 21 (8.3 overs) || {{cr|TUR}} || {{cr|CZE}} || Ilfov County || 30 August 2019\n|-\n| 2 || 28 (11.3 overs) || {{cr|TUR}