om/ci/content/records/284198.html ESPNcricinfo] (updated 22 December 2019).</small>\n|}\n\n====Most career runs====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! [[Run (cricket)|Runs]] \n! [[Innings]]\n! Player\n! Period\n|-\n| 1 || 13,296 || 396 ||[[Chris Gayle]] {{dagger}}|| 2005\u2013present\n|-\n| 2 || 10,000 || 450 ||[[Kieron Pollard]]{{dagger}}|| 2006\u2013present\n|-\n| 3 || 9,922 || 364 || [[Brendon McCullum]] || 2005\u20132019\n|-\n| 4 || 9,892 || 363 ||[[Shoaib Malik]]{{dagger}}|| 2005\u2013present\n|-\n| 5 || 9,218 || 279 ||[[David Warner (cricketer)|David Warner]]{{dagger}}|| 2007\u2013present\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" |<small>Source: [http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/284267.html ESPNcricinfo.com], last updated 17 March 2020</small>\n|}\n\n====Most centuries in a career====\n[[Chris Gayle]] is the clear leader in the list of the most career centuries in T20s with 22; only Michael Klinger (8) and David Warner (8) have scored more than seven.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/27591268/stats-gayle-stands-alone-top-t20-heap|title=Stats: Gayle stands alone at the top of the T20 heap|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=16 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/records/283756.html|title=Records {{!}} Twenty20 matches {{!}} Batting records {{!}} Most hundreds in a career {{!}} ESPNcricinfo|work=Cricinfo|access-date=2018-03-01}}</ref>\n\n====Fastest 100====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Balls\n! Player\n! Team\n! Opposition\n! Venue\n! Date\n|-\n| 1 || 30 || [[Chris Gayle]] || [[Royal Challengers Bangalore]] || [[Pune Warriors India]] || [[M. Chinnaswamy Stadium|Bangalore]] || 23 April 2013\n|-\n| 2 || 32 || [[Rishabh Pant]] ||[[Delhi cricket team|Delhi]] || [[Himachal Pradesh cricket team|Himachal Pradesh]] || [[Feroz Shah Kotla Ground|Delhi]] ||14 January 2018\n|-\n| 3 || 33 || [[Wihan Lubbe]